  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Event signatures are 32-byte hashes which are usually stored literally in the code and thus very expensive. It might be cheaper (depending on the trade-off setting) to compute them at runtime instead. We have to be careful, though, because the optimizer might actually turn it into a literal again.\r\n\r\n",
